## Backlog Prioritization Justification

The backlog was prioritized using the MoSCoW method to ensure that core system functionality is delivered first.

- **Must-have** items (e.g., device registration, intake, repair tracking) are essential for the system to function and form the foundation of the MVP.
- **Should-have** items (e.g., accessories tracking, profit calculation) add important business value but are not required for basic system operation.
- **Could-have** items (e.g., notifications, reports) improve user experience but can be implemented later without affecting core functionality.
- **Won’t-have** items (e.g., delivery staff tracking) are deferred to future iterations due to lower priority.

Story points were assigned based on estimated complexity and effort, supporting effective sprint planning.
